                <h4>Enter Sell</h4>
                <p>When the two Moving Averages cross downwards:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Guru-Angle:</strong> gives a red signal.</li>
                    <li><strong>Forex Guru Histogram Indicator:</strong> gives a red signal.</li>
                    <li><strong>Market Emotions Indicator:</strong> gives a red signal.</li>
                </ul>

                <h4>Target and Stop Loss Settings</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>15-Minute Chart:</strong> Target = 15 pips, Stop = 15 pips or Target = 20 pips, Stop = 20 pips (based on market volatility)</li>
                    <li><strong>30-Minute Chart:</strong> Target = 30 pips, Stop = 30 pips</li>
                    <li><strong>1-Hour Chart:</strong> Target = 50 pips, Stop = 50 pips</li>
                    <li><strong>4-Hour Chart:</strong> Target = 100-300 pips, Stop = 100 pips</li>
                </ul>
                <p><strong>Special Instructions for 4-Hour Chart:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Preferred to set a trailing stop of 100 pips.</li>
                    <li>Move the stop to the entry point after 100 pips, then continue to chase profits.</li>
                </ul>

                <h4>Exit Strategy</h4>
                <p>You can also exit when an opposite signal appears.</p>

